{"word":"ἀπομαγδαλία","slug":"ἀπομαγδαλία","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n13157\" key=\"a)pomagdali/a\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ἀπομαγ-δᾰλία</orth> or <orth extent=\"suff\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ἀπομαγ-λά</orth>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">ἡ</gen>, (<etym lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"etym\">ἀπομάσσω</etym>) <sense id=\"n13157.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">the crumb</tr_> or <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">inside of the loaf,</tr_> on which the Greeks wiped their hands at dinner, and then threw it to the dogs: hence, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">dog's meat,</tr_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0019.tlg002.perseus-grc1:415\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ar.\">Ar.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Eq.\">Eq.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">415</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0640.tlg001:3:44\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Alciphr.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">3.44</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0007.tlg004:12\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Plu.</author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Lyc.\">Lyc.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">12</biblScope></bibl>.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}